      • getInterNodeListener

        public java.net.URL getInterNodeListener(java.util.function.Function<java.net.URL,java.lang.Integer> portResolver)
        Determines which URL should be used to contact this node from other KSQL nodes.

        Uses INTER_NODE_LISTENER_CONFIG by default, or first listener defined in LISTENERS_CONFIG if INTER_NODE_LISTENER_CONFIG not set.

        Method takes a portResolver to resolve any auto-assigned port in LISTENERS_CONFIG, (i.e. port 0.

        Any loopback or localhost in LISTENERS_CONFIG will be replaced with local machine name, though this is not guarenteed to work across machines in all circumstance.

        Parameters:
        portResolver - called to resolve port in first LISTENERS_CONFIG if 0.
        Returns:
        the resolved inter-node endpoint to use.
